data.title: Singer Tom Jones on breaking into music and rise to stardom
data.meta_description: Sir Tom Jones has sold more than 100 million records over his remarkable six-decade career. In his new memoir, “Over the Top and Back,” Jones recounts how he rose from his roots in the coal fields of Wales to become an international singing star and an honorary knight of the realm. Anthony Mason reports.
